OL,7,FWhen members of the Scottish cabinet
OL,8,Fdiscussed the matter, in January 2010,
OL,9,Fthey therefore agreed the draft Bill
OL,10,Fshould "not at this stage set out the
OL,11,Fdate for the referendum".
OL,13,FThe paper, produced by then
OL,14,Fparliamentary business minister Bruce
OL,15,FCrawford, also noted the Scottish
OL,16,Fgovernment's proposed referendum would
OL,17,Fbe an advisory vote and would have "no
OL,18,Flegislative effect".
